In Alfamart, we have a flexible ETL system running. First, the daily runner is triggered at 21:00 PM. The system constantly looks at the input path (s3://invent-alfamart/14DC_daily_flexible) after being triggered and searches for the folders with manifest in it. It collects the folders with manifest present and copies them into the stating folder, which is deleted after completion. In Alfamart, we are using 2 batches, 7 DCs in each, by grouping the DC’s folder for ETL operations (ETL & updating the datastore( to process the data in a bulk manner. When the time is 21:55 (timeout clock), there is a time out sensor in daily_runner dag that will trigger the daily dag that will wait for batches to finish its updating datastore, and eventually trigger the rocket regular process for the night.

